## Try It Yourself

```bash
git clone https://github.com/sechan9999/RxHccNova.git
cd RxHccNova
npm install
npm run dev
# Open http://localhost:5173
```

No API key required to start. Click **"GLP-1 Off-Label Misuse"**, hit **"Analyze Claim"**, and watch the two-stage detection pipeline in action.

If you have access to Amazon Bedrock with `amazon.nova-pro-v1:0` enabled, deploy the Lambda function above and enter your API Gateway URL in the Settings panel to experience the full AI-powered analysis.

---

## Conclusion

Healthcare fraud is a solvable problem — but not with rules alone, and not with AI alone.

Amazon Nova Pro brings genuine clinical reasoning to fraud detection: it understands *why* a drug shouldn't be prescribed for a given diagnosis, not just *that* the codes don't match. Combined with a deterministic rule engine that catches 100% of known violation patterns in milliseconds, the result is a detection system that is both fast and intelligent.

The fact that this entire pipeline can be built as an open-source React application — accessible in any browser, deployable in minutes — means that even small healthcare organizations with limited IT infrastructure can start using AI-augmented fraud detection today.

The code is open. The approach is proven. And Amazon Nova makes it possible.

---

*The author built this system for the AWS Healthcare FWA Hackathon. All patient data in the application is synthetically generated — no real patient data was used or stored.*

